1.  Summary:

    This document outlines the standards and processes for contributing to the
    install-node-version script project.

2.  Contents:

    0.  METADATA ........................................................... 005
    1.  Summary ............................................................ 014
    2.  Contents ........................................................... 020
    3.  Document Status .................................................... 025
    4.  Normative Language ................................................. 030
    5.  Introduction ....................................................... 035
    6.  Workflow ........................................................... 040
    7.  Standards .......................................................... 045

3.  Document Status:

    - This document is a DRAFT repository-level RFC.
    - It is not an Internet Standards Track specification.
    - It is intended to provide contribution guidelines for this repository.

4.  Normative Language:

    - The key words "MUST", "MUST NOT", "SHOULD", and "SHOULD NOT" in this
      document SHOULD follow RFC-2119 and RFC-8174.
    - This document MUST NOT use MAY.

5.  Introduction:

    We welcome contributions to the install-node-version script! This document
    outlines the standards and processes for contributing to the project.

6.  Workflow:

    - Fork the repository.
    - Create a new branch for your feature or bug fix.
    - Ensure your code follows the 83-character column limit specified in
      .editorconfig.
    - Add detailed PowerShell Comment-Based Help to any new functions.
    - Update the CHANGELOG as needed.
    - Submit a Pull Request.

7.  Standards:

    Please refer to the README for technical specifications and design goals.
    Maintaining the RFC-style documentation and modular function design is
    mandatory for all contributions.

